  "prompt": "I am already using Reliance Jio SIM card. How to check data usage on the same ?",
  "response": "There are several ways to check your Jio data usage:\n\n**1. MyJio App (Recommended):**\n\n*   **Download & Install:** If you don't already have it, download the MyJio app from the Google Play Store (Android) or the App Store (iOS).\n*   **Login:**  Log in using your Jio mobile number and OTP (One-Time Password).\n*   **Homepage/Dashboard:** Your data balance and usage information are usually displayed prominently on the app's homepage or dashboard. You'll likely see something like \"Remaining Data: [amount] GB\" or a pie chart showing your data usage.\n*   **Detailed Usage:**  Look for a \"Usage Details,\" \"Data Usage,\" or similar option within the app (often found in the menu).  This will give you a breakdown of your daily data usage, app-wise data consumption, and other details.\n\n**2. Jio Website:**\n\n*   **Visit:** Go to the Jio website: www.jio.com\n*   **Sign In:** Click on \"Sign In\" or \"My Account\" (usually in the top right corner).\n*   **Login:** Log in using your Jio mobile number and OTP.\n*   **My Plans/Dashboard:**  After logging in, you should see a dashboard or a \"My Plans\" section where your data balance and usage information are displayed.  You can usually find more detailed usage details by navigating through the options.\n\n**3. USSD Codes (Dialer Codes):**\n\n*   **Dial a Code:**  Open your phone's dialer and dial one of the following USSD codes:\n    *   `*333#` (This is a common code)\n    *   `*111#` (Try this if *333# doesn't work)\n    *   `*1#` (Another option to try)\n*   **Check the Message:**  After dialing the code, a message will usually pop up or you'll receive an SMS with your data balance and other account details.\n\n**4. SMS (Text Message):**\n\n*   **Send an SMS:** Type `MBAL` and send it to `55333` from your Jio number.\n*   **Check Reply:** You will receive an SMS back from Jio with your data balance information.\n\n**Tips and Important Notes:**\n\n*   **MyJio App is the Easiest:** The MyJio app is generally the most user-friendly and provides the most comprehensive information.\n*   **USSD Codes May Vary:** The exact USSD codes may sometimes change, so if one doesn't work, try the others.\n*   **Data Refresh Time:** Keep in mind that data usage information may not be updated in real-time. There might be a slight delay.\n*   **JioFiber vs. Jio Mobile:** The methods described above are for Jio mobile data (SIM card). If you have JioFiber broadband, the data usage check method will be different (usually through the MyJio app, but specifically for your JioFiber account).  Make sure you are logged into the correct account in the app.\n*   **Customer Care:** If you're having trouble with any of these methods, you can contact Jio customer care for assistance.  You can usually find their contact number on the Jio website.\n\nI hope this helps!\n",
